site_description_general: 10 m upstream of culvert inlet in pool. Too shallow to sample riffle soul sample top end of shallow pool. Right bank
150m downstream of culvert on Beaver FSR upstream of first beaver dam (from culvert downstream).
comments_field: Due to shallow water depths in riffle sections sample was taken at shallow pool at the top end near where flow was entering. Two samples taken.  Fish were observed downstream of the lowest beaver dam 500m from the Fraser River. Idea is to see if we detect fish upstream of dams but downstream of the FSR. Filtering was extremely slow, so a second filter was taken, see 196076_ds_ed2b. Took water quality again this morning because has been raining heavily so wanted to see if dilution was evident through conductivity which it appears it is approximately 10% less conductivity which could impact detection ability.
methods_link1: Link to Methods1
